Program: Outlook
Title: Giving a Home to 32 Iraqi Orphans
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01mtgsz
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 12 Dec 2013
Baghdad orphanage founder Husham al-Thabe on how Mohamed al-Daradji's documentary, In My Mother's Arms, changed his fortunes. John Kani reads from Nelson Mandela's autobiography Long Walk To Freedom. In this extract, Mandela goes underground posing as a chauffeur. Nelson Mandela Mwova from Kenya and Nigerian-born Mandela Echefu on how bearing Mandela's name inspires them. Syrian artist Tammam Azzam uses digital photography to impose famous paintings onto scenes of destruction in his country. (Picture: Husham al-Thabe) Show less